Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[_Cryptosporidium_ is endemic in the USA and outbreaks in recreational water facilities like public swimming pools and fountain parks are well known. This outbreak is multicenter, which could indicate that the water used for these activities is contaminated, and not that contamination arises from introduction of fecal material into the water.

In the recommendations to users of these facilities listed above, we miss a recommendation to use diapers on children not yet trained to use a toilet. Special diapers for use in swimming pools are available. - Mod.EP

The state of Arizona can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4436035,1124. Maricopa County can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/arizona-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
